write function should be passed an obj just in case it needs to manipulate something back up in the caller.

This may have the side-effect that an ignored void *obj should be passed into __android_log_pmsg_file_write to maintain argument compatibility. We could deal with this by making it the last argument in the set and casting or requiring a static wrapper to perform this duty.

